@DFTA (Don't Feed The Animals) you need to set the environment variable correctly and it'll work but i suggest you should not do that , it will pollute the global namespace of packages. It is always better to install packages for every project. For best practices, you should even use saperate environment for every project (like dotenv or something).
but if you just want to use the package from global installation i thing setting up correct environment variable will  do the job.
& also you should feed the animals.
